Interested in testing for alflatoxins? Need free resources? This video and presentation, from the Feed the Future Innovation Lab for Livestock Systems, provides an expert's insights into sources and control of variability in aflatoxin testing. It covers sampling and testing variability and testing quality, including proficiency, traceability, and uncertainty. This presentation will help you understand the critical role of a lab in managing aflatoxin risk and the importance of a lab quality system in producing accurate, defensible and timely results. At the end, follow the instructions to enroll in a global proficiency testing program (pt.tamu.edu/) offered by the Office of the Texas State Chemist. There is no charge to participate in this ISO 17043 accredited aflatoxin proficiency-testing program. 